A pregnant woman and her two children were yesterday burnt to death at Umuoffor village, Okija in lhialla Local Government Area of Anambra State. The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Harunna Mohammed, said the cause of the fire was not yet known. It was learnt that the victims, Mrs. Nwazuru and her children, Chidiebube (two) and Makuo (one), were trapped in the inferno and were burnt beyond recognition. The police in Okija, who were at the scene of the incident, said it took the efforts of the firefighters and some sympathisers some hours to put out the fire. A neighbour to Chief Maxwel Okeke, the owner of the house, who did not want to disclose her name, blamed the incident on power surge.